To create the first user and copy the stylesheets ...

    rake typus:setup

Default user and password

    username. admin
    password. typus

== Contact

You can contact me at <fesplugas@intraducibles.net>

== Setting your own username and password

You can set your `username` and `password` overwriting the following settings:

    Typus::Configuration.options[:username] = 'username'
    Typus::Configuration.options[:password] = 'password'

You can place this settings in a initializer at `config/initializers/typus.rb`

== Configuration file options

If the configuration file is broken you'll see a `typus.yml` text on the admin interface.

=== Lists

    attribute
    attribute::OPTIONS

For example ...

    language::LANGUAGES

where `LANGUAGES` is defined at `config/initializers/typus.rb` as

    LANGUAGES = [["Català", "ca"], ["English", "en"], ["Español", "es"]]

=== Forms

    attribute::string
    attribute::text::10
    attribute::collection <= The attribute is a `belong_to :attribute` relationship.
    status::boolean
    created_at::datetime
    language::selector::LANGUAGES

=== Filters

    status::boolean
    author
    category

=== Order

    attribute::asc
    attribute::desc

=== Search

    attribute1, attribute2

== Integration with Capistrano

  deploy.task :restart, :roles => :app do
  run "cd #{current_path} && rake db:migrate RAILS_ENV=production"
    run "cd #{current_path} && rake typus:setup"
  end

Example
=======

# This Action is Accessed from the Typus controller. Before using it
# we should check the model has this actions and then check the user
# can perform this action.
def cleanup
  @model = eval params[:model].singularize.capitalize
  @model.actions.each do |action|
    @available = (params[:action].include? action[0]) ? false : true
  end
  if @available
    @model.destroy_all
    flash[:notice] = "Removed all entries."
    redirect_to :action => "index"
  else
    flunk
  end
rescue
  #else
  # flash[:notice] = "Action not available for this model."
  redirect_to :action => "index"
  # end
end

